The author reflects on the International Religious Freedom Act, which established the United States as a leader in promoting and defending freedom of religion or belief. They emphasize the importance of this freedom and express concern over the persecution and abuse faced by individuals and groups based on their religious identity. The author states that protecting religious freedom is not only a reflection of their values but also a national security priority. They pledge to continue advocating for freedom of religion or belief globally, including through multilateral coalitions. The author concludes by highlighting the need to ensure liberty for everyone, as every faith is a minority somewhere in the world.